				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I used to combine things when my game design used 16x16 metatiles... I stored the attribute of each metatile using only 2 bits, as 6 bits is a lot to waste on repeated data while they could hold other stuff about the metatile. By masking the other 6 bits off, the lower 2 could be use as an index to load a full byte with those 2 repeated from a small table ($00, $55, $AA, $FF), and then I proceeded as Disch said.
<br />
<br />It may be a little more trouble than directly loading the full byte (I'm really not gonna waste 75% of a lot of bytes), but is still cleaner than ASL'ing variable ammounts of times.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

