				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">For my routine, I actually don't use any buffers to keep track of attributes. I take the data in RAM, and store an attribute column depending on the metatile values. I've said this before, I know. I actually have my attributes updated 1 pixel after the metatile columns are updated. If they were updated the same time as my columns, the NMI routine would last way too long. So I'm never doing my Attributes at the same time as my columns, because it takes too long. I have to go, sorry.</div>

