						<div class="postbody">16 pixels is the hardware minimum, and split an attribute nybble isn't too bad (you just need to work with 4 bits a time) so you can work with vertical 16 pixel blocks and horizontal 32 pixels blocks. Else, just work with 16x16 blocks everywhere, and when you update row/colums of meatiles, just be sure to refresh just a nibble at the same time (by keeping a copy of the attribute table in RAM for example).</div>

